title: Great overnight stop
text: Stopped here overnight, room was very comfortable, large bed and staff very helpful, Covid safe environment and excellent breakfast bag and go idea. Free parking and direct access to the motorway. Pub/ restaurant on site.

title: Lovely walk and ruins.
text: Lovely ruined priory, visited church attached too. Very interesting history and old graves. Covid safe and friendly staff. Dog friendly.

title: Lovely Castle.
text: Lovely walk inside and round the outside. Lots of history. Helpful staff and covid safe. Dog friendly.

title: Very interesting.
text: Interesting history inside, walk along the ramparts. Still used by Army reserves. Covid safe and helpful staff. Dog friendly.

title: Great Castle.
text: Lovely solid castle to see inside and walk around the outside. Friendly staff and Covid safe. Lovely lake.

title: Stunning.
text: This is two houses for the price of one. The old castle and quarry gardens are lovely and the newer main hall was fascinating inside.

title: Great house and beautiful gardens.
text: Lovely garden walk, house was lovely, Covid safe enviroment and helpful staff. Dog friendly. Interesting history in the house.

title: Amazing pub.
text: Great pub, the food is excellent, landlord very social and friendly. Lovely log fire , great atmosphere.

title: Excellent food.
text: Great take away, chatty waiter, excellent choice of food and good prices too. Short wait for food in Covid safe enviroment.

title: Very informative.
text: Followed on here from Vindolanda so very informative about the soldiers and conditions they endured.

title: Great visit
text: Great visit, surprised at how large it is, beautiful to walk around. Covid safe enviroment, lovely park to the side.

title: Fantastic day out.
text: Fantastic day out, the site is huge great to walk amongst the ruins , lots of history and the museum was more than I expected. Cafe was open to sit outside and good Covid safe enviroment.

title: Great overnight stay.
text: Had to have an overnight stop, the man at reception was very helpful and fitted us in for the night. Lovely room ,clean and comfortable. Room had kettle too. Good price too. Metro station outside and plenty of shops.
place: Campanile Paris Est Porte De Bagnolet

title: Amazing restaurant,
text: Lovely setting on front, the food is delicious and well priced. It was very popular and we could see why. The staff were so friendly and helpful. Great choice on the menu and the cherry yoghurt dessert was superb.

title: Great food and staff.
text: Great food here looking out onto beach Staff very friendly especially guy out working the front, good prices and choice of food.

title: Great staff and drinks.
text: Sat here for drinks, staff very friendly, drinks good prices and overlooks the beach. Biscuits and small cake with hot drink lovely.

title: Great staff and breakfasts.
text: Had breakfast here and many evening drinks. Staff very friendly and nice environment to sit in especially in evening. Owners there too and lovely.

title: Fabulous food and staff.
text: Great food and staff so friendly. Desserts very good and caramel vodka amazing. Prices reasonable too, best to book as busy.

title: Great food and view.
text: Great food on beach front. Staff helpful and friendly. Prices very reasonable and great choice on the menu.

title: First class hotel/apartments with first class staff.
text: This resort was amazing, the staff especially Juan and guy on Saturday 15th Feb morning were so helpful to us. We changed to this resort from a previous one which was awful. Juan helped us, found an apartment available which was superb and we enjoyed the 5 days we had there. Very clean, all beautifully kept, two pool areas and lots of loungers. Apartment was clean and comfortable with all amenities we required. Lovely large patio area. Two bar/ restaurants on site with great food and drinks. Our flight was cancelled, on Sat am the gentleman at reception assisted us very well to arrange a new flight and taxi to airport. Fabulous place to stay.
place: Sunset Harbour Club by Diamond Resorts

title: Amazing.
text: What a great place to eat, the food was amazing, mixed grill , tagines especially. Also had a breakfast here. Fig jam was lovely and the rose tea superb. Staff very helpful and friendly. Would definitely go back.

title: Great breakfast.
text: Had a breakfast in here. Lovely food and drinks, good choice. Friendly staff. good prices too. Open early.

title: Great visit.
text: Great place to visit, get there early to avoid long queues. No photos allowed inside but so worth the visit, souvenir books not overly expensive.

title: Fantastic.
text: Spent hours in here, lots to see, lots of steps too. Crown jewels were amazing. Cafe not overly expensive. Get there early.

title: Great visit
text: Great place to visit, free but a donation welcome, lots to see in beautiful old rooms with seating in some.

title: First class hotel with first class staff.
text: Had a great stay here, the hotel is lovely and the staff were very helpful and friendly from the moment we arrived especially Mizan on the bar.The room was very comfortable, clean and bed comfortable too. Great location across from underground, cafes and shops. Definitely stay there next time.

title: Lovely food & atmosphere.
text: Lovely friendly restaurant, great food, plenty of choice, mussels particularly good. Staff helpful and good atmosphere inside. Prices reasonable too.

title: What a building.
text: This is huge, overwhelming really. A bit of a walk up so good shoes advisable but views amazing from top. Go early to avoid crowds. Opens at 8am.

title: Great visit, overwhelming.
text: The size of the place and the views from here are quite something. Lots of restoration going on which is quite good to see.

title: Great visit.
text: Very interesting especially after visiting the Acropolis as the artefacts you can envisage in it. 5 euros to get in seemed a great price and some ruined city directly under the museum to visit too.

title: Spectacular views.
text: Great hotel tucked in a bustling cobbled street, had a double room with terrace looking out onto the Acropolis. Comfortable bed, clean room. Slightly older fashioned but everything you need. Rooftop bar and restaurant was excellent. Staff helpful too. Breakfast was free and lots of choice.

title: Great food.
text: Great food and plenty of it, friendly staff, good prices, was open on a sunday too. Very nice wine, worth a visit.

title: Great food.
text: Had a lunch here the soup was lovely. Quaint little restaurant tucked away in the latin quarter. Very friendly staff and lovely food. Good prices.

title: What an amazing restaurant.
text: This place is like stepping back in time to an old luxurious train carriage, the furnishings are great, quite intimate. The staff were lovely and the food was good too, big servings, lovely wine and not too expensive. A real find.

title: Wow what a stadium.
text: This arena is amazing, went to a rugby match, felt like a concert, the lights and sounds were superb. Felt cosy inside not too big.

title: Great visit.
text: Was not expecting to see a live court case but did, great historical building , lovely architecture all the way round.

title: Great building, lots to see.
text: Found by accident, has Marie Antoinettes cell inside and revolution prison. Beautiful arch ceilings in main area.

title: Wow, stunning.
text: This place is a must, probably looked over before Notre Dame fire but well worth the visit. The stained glass windows and ceilings are beautiful.

title: Overnight stop was perfect.
text: Lovely hotel tucked away off main street. Room was good, roomy, clean and comfortable. Very close to metro, shops and restaurants. Good price too. Staff friendly, has a lift, clean small bathroom. A good stopover.

title: Beautiful city.
text: The old town of Split is lovely to walk around with lots of shops, bars and restuarants. The narrow streets are filled with beautiful architecture and quaint areas.

title: Buzzy place to eat.
text: Great restaurant on harbour side with music. Good food and good prices. Had a lunch there. Staff helpful and friendly.

title: Great trip.
text: We did the half day trip on the blue line to Salona, Trogir and Klis Fortress. It was a lovely day out with Barbara our guide. She was very helpful and friendly. Excellent value. We then did the red line round Split with Doris also very friendly . Well worth the money.

title: Bizarre.
text: Was recommended by a friend to visit this and a very strange place it is. The noise made by the sea on the wall is just like a mouth organ but louder.

title: Beautiful.
text: Stopped off on our tour to visit this lovely cathedral. Had a treasury room which held many church books, silver and ornamental artefacts.
place: The Cathedral of St James in Sibenik

title: Good place to sit.
text: Good spot to sit harbour side to have a drink. Food reasonable price too. Staff were reasonably friendly.

title: Great place to sit.
text: Lovely atmosphere here, cafe luxor inside this area for drinks. Roman soldiers dressed up make this a special place offering photos with them. The palace itself is huge and very interesting.

title: Loved Bobis.
text: These are all over Split but great for pastries, ice creams and drinks. Lovely staff and one on harbour front was great. Good prices.

title: Great ice cream
text: Had ice cream here, was lovely,a friendly lad behind counter. A lovely little find, prices good too.

title: Amazing.
text: Part of the bus tour we were on, great views from top , bit of a walk but very interesting especially if a game of thrones fan.

title: Great food.
text: Good atmosphere here, lovely food and good choice. Staff friendly and prices good. Was quite busy and despite some poor reviews we enjoyed it.

title: Great Food.
text: Great restaurant with friendly staff. Good prices and lots to choose from on menu. Tucked away in lovely street.

title: Lovely food.
text: Great food and atmosphere. Prices good for waterside restaurant. Good choice of food. Friendly staff.

title: Beautiful old town
text: Quite easy to walk around as on small island. Lovely old streets with lots of restaurants and bars. Shops too. Lovely harbour with boat trips. Cathedral a must and town square.

title: Lovely friendly hotel.
text: Great hotel, room was beautifully decorated , clean and comfortable. The staff were lovely, Joseph and Christina very helpful and friendly. Lovely outside area to sit with soft furnishings, couches and lounge areas. Fabulous view over to Trogir, a two minute walk from hotel. Good breakfast and desserts. Parking available in nearby car park for 5 euros. Loved it.

title: Wow stunning.
text: A boat trip and walk leads you to this wonderful set of terraced falls. The scenery and water is amazing. Wear good shoes.

title: Great overnight stay.
text: Lovely hotel and restaurant for our one night stay. good breakfast included. Bed very comfortable and clean room. Location good two minute walk to harbour front, boat trips and bars.Friendly staff and waiters in restaurant.

title: Lovely food.
text: Had evening meal here. Very good choice and prices too. Fish was lovely then sat in the bar. Outside area to sit overlooking lake.

title: Fantastic experience. Overwhelming.
text: What a wonderful place, the scenery, views, walks and waterfalls are magical. Stayed in hotel next to entrance 2 . The wooden walkway over some of the falls is quite amazing. Wear decent footwear/walking shoes. Was very busy even end of Sept. Boat trip back too.

title: Great location.
text: Great location next to entrance 2 of the lakes. Clean and comfortable with good choice of breakfast. Hotel next door did evening meals. Friendly staff, comfortable bed and room had a balcony. Clean bathroom.

title: Excellent restaurant and staff.
text: Great meal, lots of choice and very friendly staff. On harbour front. Prices very good and great desserts.
